      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The English language has shed thousands of words over the centuries — but the Scrabble dictionary hasn't. Words that Shakespeare would recognise still sit comfortably in both SOWPODS and TWL, and many are surprisingly useful for scoring. Here's your guide to archaic words that can win you games.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why Archaic Words Matter in Scrabble</h2>

